      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <!--
Comments below by Csaba Kiss and Dániel Balogh (BD) are offered "as is" and do not represent a thoroughly researched or considered opinion.
-->
        <!--
1 Sircar, D.C. & Singh Deo, J.T., 'Amgura plates of Jayarāja of Śarabhapura,
regnal year 3', Indian Museum Bulletin, January 1976, pp.57-59
&
I only used this (not given in Michael's map):
2 Shastri, A. M., Inscriptions of the Śarabhapurīyas, Pāṇḍuvaṁśins and Somavaṁśins,
Part II Inscriptions, Motilal Bandarsidass, Delhi, 1995, pp.14-16
-->
        <div n="A" type="textpart">
          <head xml:lang="eng">Seal</head>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="1">
            <lb n="1"/>
            <l n="a">prasanna-<unclear>tanayasyedaṁ</unclear></l>
            <l n="b">vikkramākkrā<supplied reason="omitted">n</supplied>ta-vidviṣaḥ</l>
            <!--
seal.1. D. Balogh: Shastri reads prasanna-hr̥dayasaiva, marking only hr̥ as unclear. The facsimile in Shastri is unclear. Given the parallel seals, not known to Fleet, I'm convinced the correct reading is prasanna-tanayasyedaṁ. Sircar_1959-60f:156 suggests the same.
-->
            <lb n="2"/>
            <l n="c">
              <unclear>śrīmato jayarājasya</unclear>
            </l>
            <l n="d">śāsana<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> ripu-śāsana<supplied reason="omitted">M</supplied></l>
          </lg>
        </div>
        <div n="B" type="textpart">
          <head xml:lang="eng">Plates</head>
          <p><pb n="1v"/><lb n="1"/><g type="mangala"/>
svasti śarabha-purāt parama-bhāgavato mātā-pitr̥-pādānu<lb break="no" n="2"/>ddhyātaś śrī-mahājayarāja<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied>
sāmparāja-bhuktīya-rājya-grāme pra<lb break="no" n="3"/>tivāsinas samājñāpayati</p>
          <p>viditam astu vo yathāsmā<lb break="no" n="4"/>bhir ayaṁ grāmo vājasaneya-kauśika-sagotra-brāhmaṇa-viṣṇusvā<lb break="no" n="5"/>mine mātā-pitror ātmanaś ca puṇyābhivr̥ddhaye Udaka-pūrvva<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> tāmra-
						<pb n="2r"/><lb n="6"/>śāsanenātisr̥ṣṭas te yūyam evopalabhyāsyājñā-śravaṇa-vidheyā bhū<!--
L6. Shastri says: "Read yūyam evam upalabhyāsyā-"
--><lb break="no" n="7"/>tvā yathocitaṁ bhoga-bhāgam upaneṣyatha<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied><!--
L7. Usually we have -bhāgam upanayantaḥ [ūpa- Shastri] sukhaṁ prativatsyatha.
-->bhaviṣyataś ca bhūmi-pālā<lb break="no" n="8"/>n bodhayati<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied><!--
L8. Usually we have bhūmi-pān anudarśayati here.
-->bhavadbhir apy asyā datte<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> pratipālanaṁ karttavya<lb break="no" n="9"/>m ataś ca vyāsa-gītān api ślokān udāhara<choice>
              <sic>ṁ</sic>
              <corr>n</corr>
            </choice>ti</p>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="1">
            <l n="a">bahubhir vvasudhā <lb n="10"/>dattā</l>
            <l n="b">rājabhis sagarādibhiḥ</l>
            <l n="c">yasya yasya yadā bhūmis</l>
            <l n="d">tasya tasya
								<pb n="2v"/><lb n="11"/>tadā phala<choice>
                <sic>ṁ</sic>
                <corr>M</corr>
              </choice></l>
          </lg>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="2">
            <l n="a">sva-dattā<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> para-dattāṁ vā</l>
            <l n="b">yatnād rakṣa yudhiṣṭhira</l>
            <l n="c">ma<lb break="no" n="12"/>hī<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> mahīmatā<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> śreṣṭha</l>
            <!--
L12. Still to decide if mahīmatāṁ or mahimatāṁ is the one to prefer.
-->
            <l n="d">dānāc chreyo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>nupālana<choice>
                <sic>ṁ</sic>
                <corr>M</corr>
              </choice>|</l>
          </lg>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="3">
            <l n="a">ṣaṣṭi<surplus>m</surplus>-varṣa<lb break="no" n="13"/>-sahasrāṇi</l>
            <l n="b">svargge vasati bhūmi-da<unclear>ḥ</unclear></l>
            <l n="c">ācche<choice>
                <sic>p</sic>
                <corr>t</corr>
              </choice>tā cā<!--
D. Balogh: I'm not sure āccheptā should be emended to ācchettā (as Shastri does). This is an interesting bridge between the variants ākṣeptā and ācchettā; either may have been the composer's intent.
--><lb break="no" n="14"/>numantā ca</l>
            <l n="d">tā<choice>
                <sic>t</sic>
                <corr>n</corr>
              </choice>y eva narake vase<unclear>T</unclear></l>
            <!--
L14. tātyeva in Shastri could be a typo .
-->
          </lg>
          <lg met="indravajrā" n="4">
            <!--
Garuḍapurāṇa 2.42.4
-->
            <l n="a">agner apatyaṁ prathamaṁ <lb n="15"/>suvarṇṇaṁ</l>
            <l n="b">bhūr vvaiṣṇavī sūryya-sutāś ca gāva<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied></l>
            <l n="c">lokās traya<pb break="no" n="3r"/><lb break="no" n="16"/>s tena bhava<surplus>ṁ</surplus><choice>
                <sic>t</sic>
                <corr>n</corr>
              </choice>ti
dattāḥ||</l>
            <!--
L16. Note that lokās and dattāḥ are swapped here as compared to other similar passages.
-->
            <l n="d">yaẖ kāñcanaṁ gāñ ca mahīñ ca dadyā<lb break="no" n="17"/>d</l>
          </lg>
          <p>iti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> dūtakam adhikaraṇa<supplied reason="omitted">M</supplied><supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
svamukhājñayā ca pravarddhamāna-vi<lb break="no" n="18"/>jaya-s<choice>
              <sic>āv</sic>
              <corr>aṁ</corr>
            </choice>vats<choice>
              <sic>ā</sic>
              <corr>a</corr>
            </choice>ra
						<num value="3">3</num> māgha <num value="7">7</num> U<choice>
              <sic>kti</sic>
              <corr>tkī</corr>
            </choice>rṇṇa<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> suvarṇṇā<lb break="no" n="19"/>kārācalasiṅghena||
</p>
        </div>
      </div>
